Tutorial for a first implementation of path integral Monte Carlo (PIMC)

Step 1. sample the exact density matrix (DM) with Monte Carlo
Step 2. build exact DM with exact link action using path integral (PI)
Step 3. PIMC for simple harmonic oscillator (SHO) using exact link action
Step 4. approximate the exact link action with primitive approximation
Step 5. PIMC for simple harmonic oscillator (SHO) using primitive link action

Improvements:
1. efficienty wiggling of path: eg. bisection move (build on step 2)
2. better approximation of link action: eg. Feynman-Kac (build on step 3)
3. calculate other observables: eg. kinetic energy (build on step 2)

Next:
2 Boltzmannons in a harmonic well/quantum dot
2 Bosons in a harmonic well
2 Fermions in a harmonic well
